      "content": "it's hard to believe there's an identity outside of this. i've spent my whole adult life in labs and libraries. everyone \"helps\" by telling me to find a new hobby or that i'm more than my work, but that feels like such a lie. it doesn't change the fact that the career i built is gone. everything is just static and noise now. when i think about \"navigating the crisis,\" it just feels like more work, more talking, more performing. i don't want to navigate it. i just want the peace of not being me anymore. is that even a rational thing to want? to just want the end of the struggle?",
