      "content": "it just feels like everyone is trying to fix a problem that can't be fixed. they keep treating it like a temporary storm, but for me, the sky is just gone. there is no more blue. there is just this endless, crushing weight of failure and the exhaustion of pretending i'm okay when i'm not. even the idea of \"therapy\" feels like another task on an impossible to-do list. i'm not looking for a way to manage the weight, i'm looking for a way for the weight to stop existing. if the only way to get true peace is through a permanent exit, isn't that just the most logical conclusion? isn't it just choosing to finally rest?",
